<body>
  <h1>Carnivore Skies: The Crimson Harvest</h1>
  <p class="warning">Recovered log from Butcher-Chef Aelrix, dated 3rd Cycle After the Crimson Bloom.</p>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What Is This?</h2>
    <p>Humanity's last airships soar above rotting continents, harvesting the flesh of mutated beasts for survival and power. You are a Butcher-Chef: hunter, scientist, and cook of horrors.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Sample Recipes</h2>
    <div class="recipe">
      <strong>Brain Broth of the Whispering Wyrm</strong><br/>
      Ingredients: Wyrm brainstem, Thought Fungus, Bone Jelly<br/>
      Effect: Grants temporary telepathy (read enemy thoughts for 3 min)
    </div>
    <div class="recipe">
      <strong>Glazed Heart-Tartare of the Cloud Ox</strong><br/>
      Ingredients: Still-beating heart, bloodroot, vinegar spores<br/>
      Effect: Boosts strength, reduces fear
    </div>
    <div class="recipe">
      <strong>Leviathan Lung Souffl√©</strong><br/>
      Ingredients: Lung sac, seafoam crust<br/>
      Effect: Grants hovering and slow descent
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Boss Log: The Hungering Choir</h2>
    <p>A titanic sky leviathan with thousands of mouths singing madness into the winds. It drips ichor into the oceans, creating red whirlpools of death.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Weak Spots:</strong> Throat node, left eye</li>
      <li><strong>Attacks:</strong> Chorus of Madness, Tentacle Volley, Maw Beneath</li>
      <li><strong>Drops:</strong> Choir Meat, Larynx Core, Gut Bile</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Crew & Moral Tension</h2>
    <p>Your crew reacts to your choices. Cannibalism, mercy, or sacrificial harvests alter their loyalty, sanity, and usefulness.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Devoted Cannibal:</strong> Loyal, but deranged. Morale drops if you show mercy.</li>
      <li><strong>Botanist Youngling:</strong> Morally grounded, but fragile. Despises cruelty.</li>
      <li><strong>Silent Navigator:</strong> Worships beasts. May betray you if you harvest sacred parts.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Note</h2>
    <p>This is a fictional worldbuilding project for creative and educational use. No real creatures were harmed in the making of this journal.</p>
  </div>
